        "text": "*[Bug 18989] Wishlist: provide conversion of POSIXlt time zone retaining sub-second accuracy*\n<https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=18989>\n\n--- Comment #21 from Suharto Anggono (<mailto:suharto_anggono@yahoo.com|suharto_anggono@yahoo.com>) ---\n(In reply to Suharto Anggono from comment #20)\n&gt; x2 &lt;- x1 &lt;- as.POSIXlt(.POSIXct(numeric(2), tz = \"UTC\"))\n&gt; x1[1:2] &lt;- y &lt;- c(\"2006-02-20 11:16:16.683000\", \"9999-12-31 23:59:59.999999\")\n&gt; x2[[1L]] &lt;- y[[1L]]; x2[[2L]] &lt;- y[[2L]]\n&gt; \n&gt; R 4.5.3: as.POSIXlt(*)\n&gt; R 4.6.0: as.POSIXlt(as.POSIXct(*), tz = *)\n&gt; r89926:\n&gt; [&lt;- :\n&gt; - attr(as.POSIXlt(*), \"tzone\") is \"UTC\": as.POSIXlt(*)\n&gt; - else: as.POSIXlt(*) then as.POSIXlt(as.POSIXct(*), tz = *) then correct sec\n&gt; [[&lt;- : as.POSIXlt(as.POSIXct(*), tz = *)\n&gt; \n[...]\n&gt; \n&gt; x1$sec %% 1 == as.numeric(substring(y, 18)) %% 1\n&gt; R 4.5.3: TRUE TRUE\n&gt; R 4.6.0: FALSE FALSE\n&gt; r89926: TRUE TRUE\n&gt; \n[...]\n&gt; \n&gt; x2$sec %% 1 == as.numeric(substring(y, 18)) %% 1\n&gt; R 4.5.3: TRUE TRUE\n&gt; R 4.6.0, r89926: FALSE FALSE\n&gt; *floor sec before as.POSIXct: TRUE TRUE\n\nCould also be\n\nsubstring(format(x1, \"%OS6\"), 4) == substring(y, 21)\nR 4.5.3: TRUE TRUE\nR 4.6.0: TRUE FALSE\nr89926: TRUE TRUE\n\nsubstring(format(x2, \"%OS6\"), 4) == substring(y, 21)\nR 4.5.3: TRUE TRUE\nR 4.6.0, r89926: TRUE FALSE\n*floor sec before as.POSIXct: TRUE TRUE",
