        "text": "*[Bug 19060] New: Fix build on distros that package with --package-metadata*\n<https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=19060>\n\n            Bug ID: 19060\n           Summary: Fix build on distros that package with\n                    --package-metadata\n           Product: R\n           Version: R 4.6.x\n          Hardware: Other\n                OS: Other\n            Status: UNCONFIRMED\n          Severity: normal\n          Priority: P5\n         Component: Misc\n          Assignee: <mailto:R-core@R-project.org|R-core@R-project.org>\n          Reporter: <mailto:jeroenooms@gmail.com|jeroenooms@gmail.com>\n\nWe found that the r-base debian package fails to build on Ubuntu 26.04 (even\nthough it succeeds to build manually). The bug is caused by a `sed` command in\nsrc\/unix\/Makefile.in which uses a colon as the delimiter. \n\nRecent Linux distros add `--package-metadata=...` to the LDFLAGS, and the value\nfor this flag contains colons. So the minimal fix is to use another delimiter\nin sed, e.g: <https:\/\/github.com\/r-devel\/r-svn\/pull\/253.diff>\n\nFor more details see <https:\/\/github.com\/r-devel\/r-svn\/pull\/253>",
        "username": "r-bugs notifier",
        "icons": {
            "emoji": ":robot_face:"
